.TH EODINGA 1 "2026-04-23" "eodinga 0.1.130" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
eodinga \- local-first lexical file search for Windows and Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eodinga
[\-h] [\-\-log\-level LOG_LEVEL] [\-\-config CONFIG] [\-\-db DB]
\fICOMMAND\fR ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Indexes filenames, paths, and optional parsed document text into a local SQLite/FTS5 database, then exposes the same search engine through CLI, GUI, and launcher surfaces.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-level LOG_LEVEL\fR
argparse option exported from the shipped CLI surface.
.TP
\fB\-\-config CONFIG\fR
argparse option exported from the shipped CLI surface.
.TP
\fB\-\-db DB\fR
argparse option exported from the shipped CLI surface.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBindex\fR
usage: eodinga index [\-h] [\-\-root ROOT] [\-\-rebuild]
.TP
\fBwatch\fR
usage: eodinga watch [\-h]
.TP
\fBsearch\fR
usage: eodinga search [\-h] [\-\-json] [\-\-limit LIMIT] [\-\-root ROOT] query
.TP
\fBstats\fR
usage: eodinga stats [\-h] [\-\-json]
.TP
\fBgui\fR
usage: eodinga gui [\-h] [\-\-test\-mode]
.TP
\fBdoctor\fR
usage: eodinga doctor [\-h]
.TP
\fBversion\fR
usage: eodinga version [\-h]
